keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_OPENDET
keys.description: Enable open antenna detection flag. Used by EXT and MADC engines.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_OPENDET_POL
keys.description: Open antenna detection polarity. Set to true if polarity of the antenna open detection is active low. Used by EXT engine.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_PWRDOWN
keys.description: Power down antenna flag. Enable power down antenna logic in the event of antenna short circuit. CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_SHORTDET must be enabled to use this feature. Used by EXT and MADC engines.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_PWRDOWN_POL
keys.description: Power down antenna logic polarity. Set to true if polarity of the antenna power down logic is active high. Used by EXT and MADC engines.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_RECOVER
keys.description: Automatic recovery from short state flag. Enable automatic recovery from short state. Used by EXT and MADC engines.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_SHORTDET
keys.description: Enable short antenna detection flag. Used by EXT and MADC engines.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_SHORTDET_POL
keys.description: Short antenna detection polarity. Set to true if polarity of the antenna short detection is active low. Used by EXT engine.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_VOLTCTRL
keys.description: Active antenna voltage control flag. Used by EXT and MADC engines.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_ON_SHORT_US
keys.description: ANT on->short timeout [us]. Delay in microseconds between turning the antenna power supply on and enabling the antenna short circuit detection.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_SUP_ENGINE
keys.description: Antenna supervisor engine selection. Select the engine used to evaluate antenna state. The EXT engine uses an external comparator for current measurement. The MADC engine uses built-in measurement ADC and requires only a shunt resistor for current measurement. The MADC engine is supported only in selected u-blox generation 9 receivers.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_SUP_OPEN_PIN
keys.description: ANT2 PIO number. Antenna Switch (ANT2) PIO number. Used by EXT engine.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_SUP_OPEN_THR
keys.description: Antenna supervisor MADC engine open detection threshold. Threshold below which antenna open/disconnected is detected. Used by MADC engine.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_SUP_SHORT_PIN
keys.description: ANTO PIO number. Antenna Short (ANTO) PIO number. Used by EXT engine.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_SUP_SHORT_THR
keys.description: Antenna supervisor MADC engine short detection threshold. Threshold above which antenna short is detected. Used by MADC engine.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_SUP_SWITCH_PIN
keys.description: ANT1 PIO number. Antenna Switch (ANT1) PIO number. Used by EXT and MADC engines.

keys.description: Set to true when all filter settings are to be applied, not just recording enabling/disabling.

keys.name: CFG-LOGFILTER-MIN_INTERVAL
keys.description: Minimum time interval between logged positions (0 = not set). This is only applied in combination with the speed and/or position thresholds. If both MIN_INTERVAL and TIME_THRS are set, MIN_INTERVAL must be less than or equal to TIME_THRS.

keys.name: CFG-LOGFILTER-ONCE_PER_WAKE_UP_ENA
keys.description: Set to true recording only one single position per PSM on/off mode wake-up period is enabled.

keys.name: CFG-LOGFILTER-POSITION_THRS
keys.description: If the 3D position difference is greater than the threshold then the position is logged (0 = not set). MIN_INTERVAL also applies.

keys.name: CFG-LOGFILTER-RECORD_ENA
keys.description: Set to true when recording enabled.

keys.name: CFG-LOGFILTER-SPEED_THRS
keys.description: If the current speed is greater than the threshold then the position is logged (0 = not set). MIN_INTERVAL also applies.

keys.name: CFG-LOGFILTER-TIME_THRS
keys.description: If the time difference is greater than the threshold then the position is logged (0 = not set).

keys.name: CFG-MOT-GNSSDIST_THRS
keys.description: Distance above which GNSS-based stationary motion is exit (a.k.a. static hold distance threshold)

keys.name: CFG-PM-ACQPERIOD
keys.description:
Acquisition period used if the receiver previously
failed to achieve a position fix.
If set to 0, the receiver will never retry an acquisition and will wait for external events.

keys.name: CFG-PM-DONOTENTEROFF
keys.description:
Behavior of receiver in case it cannot achieve a
position fix during a position update period.
Disable to make the receiver enter (Inactive) Awaiting next search state, enable to make the receiver not enter (Inactive)
Awaiting next search state but keep trying to acquire a fix instead.

keys.name: CFG-PM-EXTINTBACKUP
keys.description: EXTINT pin control (Backup)

keys.name: CFG-PM-EXTINTINACTIVE
keys.description:
EXTINT pin control (Inactive)
Enable to force backup in case EXTINT pin is inactive for time longer than CFG-PM-EXTINTINACTIVITY.

keys.name: CFG-PM-EXTINTINACTIVITY
keys.description: Inactivity time out on EXTINT pin if enabled

keys.name: CFG-PM-EXTINTSEL
keys.description: EXTINT pin select

keys.name: CFG-PM-EXTINTWAKE
keys.description: EXTINT pin control (Wake)

keys.name: CFG-PM-GRIDOFFSET
keys.description:
Position update period grid offset relative to
GPS start of week.
If set to 0, the position update periods are aligned to the GPS week.

keys.name: CFG-PM-LIMITPEAKCURR
keys.description: Limit peak current

keys.name: CFG-PM-MAXACQTIME
keys.description:
Maximum time to spend in Acquisition state
If 0: bound disabled (see the Maximum startup state duration section in the integration manual for details).

keys.name: CFG-PM-MINACQTIME
keys.description: Minimum time to spend in Acquisition state

keys.name: CFG-PM-ONTIME
keys.description:
Time to stay in Tracking state.
If set to 0, the receiver will only very briefly enter tracking state (after acquisition) and then go back to inactive.

keys.name: CFG-PM-OPERATEMODE
keys.description:
General mode of operation.
Setting this to either PSMOO or PSMCT will turn the corresponding mode on. Setting this to FULL will turn any PSM off.
See the integration manual for details.

FULL.description: normal operation, no power save mode active

keys.name: CFG-PM-POSUPDATEPERIOD
keys.description:
Position update period for PSMOO.
Allowed range: >= 5 s and smaller than the number of seconds in a week. If set to 0, the receiver will never retry a fix and
will wait for external events.

keys.name: CFG-PM-UPDATEEPH
keys.description:
Update ephemeris regularly.
Disable to not wake up to update ephemeris data, enable adds extra wakeup cycles to update the ephemeris data.

keys.name: CFG-PM-WAITTIMEFIX
keys.description:
Wait for time fix
Disable to wait for normal fix OK before starting ONTIME, enable to wait for time fix OK before starting ONTIME.
